Description: Cladina portentosa subsp. pacific and Cladina rangiferina
logging road, seral stage mixed forest
On sandstone cliffs, on enclave with Allium acuminatum, Camas liechnitti; aspect south 28 degrees west.
Seaside sandstone clifftop, full sun; beside single A. columbiana, A. uva-ursi seen down by shoreline.
Moist track through forest opening; disturbed seepy sites with Gnaphalium palustre, Juncus bufonius, J. effusus subsp. pacificus, Hypericum anagalloides, Spiranthes romanzoffiana.
Moist track through forest opening; bare soil with Gnaphalium palustre, Juncus bufonius, J. effusus subsp. pacificus, Hypericum anagalloides.
On shallow soil over bedrock in seepage area; asp. N 54 degrees E, 15 percent slope.
Trackside water pool on grassy bank.
Seaside sandstone cliffs in cracks near high tide line, with Lonicera hispidula, Paxistima myrsinites.
